  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "peripheral-arterial-disease",
  "name": "PAD - Medication Query (Cilostazol + Antiplatelets + Statin)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find PAD patients via medications. PAD treatment combines: cilostazol (PAD-specific phosphodiesterase inhibitor for claudication), pentoxifylline (PAD/claudication), aspirin/clopidogrel (antiplatelets, also used for CHD/VTE), and atorvastatin (statin, shared with FH/CHD). Cilostazol is the most PAD-specific marker.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed peripheral arterial disease medications including cilostazol, pentoxifylline, aspirin, clopidogrel, or atorvastatin.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on PAD medications.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed peripheral arterial disease medications — phosphodiesterase inhibitors for claudication (cilostazol, pentoxifylline), antiplatelets for atherothrombotic prevention (aspirin, clopidogrel), and statin for atherosclerosis (atorvastatin).",
    "expert": "I need MedicationRequest resources for any PAD therapy. Use these RxNorm ingredient codes: 21107 (cilostazol — PAD-specific PDE3 inhibitor for claudication), 8013 (pentoxifylline — PAD/claudication), 1191 (aspirin), 32968 (clopidogrel), 83367 (atorvastatin). Combine in a single comma-separated code search. Cilostazol/pentoxifylline are PAD-specific; aspirin/clopidogrel/atorvastatin have heavy cross-indication with CHD/VTE/FH."
  },
